The paper deals with the placement of an aerial base station in a wireless network to improve the quality of service (QoS) for mobile users. This involves optimizing the placement of the aerial base station in a 3D environment, which is a problem in network optimization and control. The proposed approach uses reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
